# Standards

## Principle

File size limits are context engineering.
Every file fits in a context window. Linter enforces this.

---

## Limits

Defined in `pyproject.toml` `[tool.agent-lint]`, enforced by `./agent lint`.
When exceeded: split into submodules or extract to separate module.

---

## Code Rules

- Module docstring required for every .py file
- Type hints required on public function signatures (not `_private`)
- Linter reads .gitignore and skips excluded paths
- DRY: single source of truth per concept — no duplicated logic between modules

---

## Verification

**Verified facts only.** No estimates, no assumed metrics.

| Level | Name | Meaning |
|-------|------|---------|
| L1 | Hypothesis | Unverified, in PLAN.md |
| L2 | Sampled | Partial coverage |
| L3 | Verified | Full coverage |

NEVER: generate counts without query, hardcode or persist derived metrics
(in code or conversation), use "approximately/~", assume system state

ALWAYS: run query → show result, state coverage %, mark hypotheses in PLAN.md
